      "side": 1,
      "message": "Also wanted to say that it seems std::launder is insane in that while it is called \u0027Pointer optimization barrier\u0027 in the specification, it requires that an actual object X be present at the location pointed to, so it cannot be used to obtain a X* of a zero sized container (which is at least one reason why patch set 1 doesn\u0027t fulfill the requirements). It\u0027s more of a \u0027Pointer to complete object optimization barrier\u0027. (It\u0027s kinda like the reason for \u0027meow::data()\u0027 since \u0027\u0026meow::[0]\u0027 fails on empty containers.) Now, in theory this shouldn\u0027t make a difference since you couldn\u0027t access anything through an X* of a zero sized container, but on the other hand calling std::launder on such a thing is technically UB! So I think SkTArray::data would need to be careful not to call \u0027std::launder(fItemArray)\u0027 when empty, since that would technically be undefined behavior.",
      "parentUuid": "ef95a66e_86f267b9",
      "revId": "deaf44729d054cc77b7207706a957b8902bbef34",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
